The low level of participation in the VFW by 'NamVets on the onset is probably the reason for the continued heavy focus of those organizations on the Korean War and back. I did not join either of those organizations in the early 70's because of the membership's consistantly reported unfriendly attitude toward Vietnam Veterans. <br><br>
With the hostile/intolerant/discriminatory attitude in the general population of the early 70's toward the Vietnam Veteran which I experienced, the fit was there, and I chose to go underground, remain silent, and stay out of the mainstream.<br><br>
I now belong to the VFW, but it is at arms length. Although I have not experienced anything like the stuff of the 70's, I am still gunshy, and time will tell. It seems like the Gulf War enjoys more acceptance, but my sensitivities may be still distorting the view. 
